\c 1
\ms1 A prophecy from John
\p
\v 1 This is what God showed to Jesus Christ, so that he could tell his servants what must happen soon. Christ then sent his angel with the message to his servant John.
\v 2 And John told everything that he had seen about God's message and about what Jesus Christ had said and done.
\p
\v 3 God will bless everyone who reads this prophecy to others,\f + \fr 1.3 \fq who reads this prophecy to others: \ft A public reading, in a worship service.\f* and he will bless everyone who hears and obeys it. The time is almost here.
\p
\v 4 From John to the seven churches in Asia.\f + \fr 1.4 \fq Asia: \ft The section 1.4—3.22 is in the form of a letter. Asia was in the eastern part of the Roman Empire and is present day Turkey.\f*\x - \xo 1.4: a \xt Ex 3.14; \xo b \xt Rev 4.5.\x*
\q1 I pray that you
\q2 will be blessed
\q1 with kindness and peace
\q1 from God, who is and was
\q2 and is coming.
\q1 May you receive
\q2 kindness and peace
\q1 from the seven spirits
\q2 before the throne of God.
\q1
\v 5 May kindness and peace\x - \xo 1.5: a \xt Is 55.4; \xo b \xt Ps 89.27.\x*
\q2 be yours
\q1 from Jesus Christ,
\q2 the faithful witness.
\b
\q1 Jesus was the first
\q2 to conquer death,
\q1 and he is the ruler
\q2 of all earthly kings.
\q1 Christ loves us,
\q2 and by his blood
\q1 he set us free
\q2 from our sins.
\q1
\v 6 He lets us rule as kings\x - \xo 1.6: \xt Ex 19.6; Rev 5.10.\x*
\q1 and serve God his Father
\q2 as priests.
\q1 To him be glory and power
\q2 for ever and ever! Amen.
\q1
\v 7 Look! He is coming\x - \xo 1.7: a \xt Dn 7.13; Mt 24.30; Mk 13.26; Lk 21.27; 1 Th 4.17; \xo b \xt Zec 12.10; Jn 19.34,37; \xo c \xt Zec 12.10; Mt 24.30.\x*
\q2 with the clouds.
\q1 Everyone will see him,
\q1 even the ones who stuck
\q2 a sword through him.
\q1 All people on earth
\q1 will weep because of him.
\q2 Yes, it will happen! Amen.
\p
\v 8 The Lord God says, “I am Alpha and Omega,\f + \fr 1.8 \fq Alpha and Omega: \ft The first and last letters of the Greek alphabet, which sometimes mean “first” and “last”.\f* the one who is and was and is coming. I am God All-Powerful!”\x - \xo 1.8: a \xt Rev 22.13; \xo b \xt Ex 3.14.\x*
\ms1 A vision of the living Lord
\s1 A vision of the risen Lord
\p
\v 9 I am John, a follower together with all of you. We suffer because Jesus is our king, but he gives us the strength to endure. I was sent to Patmos Island,\f + \fr 1.9 \fq Patmos Island: \ft A small island where prisoners were sometimes kept by the Romans.\f* because I had preached God's message and had told about Jesus.
\v 10 On the Lord's day the Spirit took control of me, and behind me I heard a loud voice that sounded like a trumpet.
\v 11 The voice said, “Write in a book what you see. Then send it to the seven churches in Ephesus, Smyrna, Pergamum, Thyatira, Sardis, Philadelphia, and Laodicea.”\f + \fr 1.11 \fq Ephesus...Laodicea: \ft Ephesus was in the centre with the six other cities forming a half-circle around it.\f*
\p
\v 12 When I turned to see who was speaking to me, I saw seven gold lampstands.
\v 13 There with the lampstands was someone who seemed to be the Son of Man.\f + \fr 1.13 \fq Son of Man: \ft That is, Jesus.\f* He was wearing a robe that reached down to his feet, and a gold cloth was wrapped around his chest.\x - \xo 1.13: a \xt Dn 7.13; \xo b \xt Dn 10.5.\x*
\v 14 His head and his hair were white as wool or snow, and his eyes looked like flames of fire.\x - \xo 1.14: \xt Dn 7.9.\x*\x - \xo 1.14,15: \xt Dn 10.6.\x*
\v 15 His feet were glowing like bronze being heated in a furnace, and his voice sounded like the roar of a waterfall.\x - \xo 1.15: \xt Ez 1.24; 43.2.\x*
\v 16 He held seven stars in his right hand, and a sharp double-edged sword was coming from his mouth. His face was shining as bright as the sun at midday.
\p
\v 17 When I saw him, I fell at his feet like a dead person. But he put his right hand on me and said:\x - \xo 1.17: \xt Is 44.6; 48.12; Rev 2.8; 22.13.\x*
\pi Don't be afraid! I am the first, the last,
\v 18 and the living one. I died, but now I am alive for evermore, and I have the keys to death and the world of the dead.\f + \fr 1.18 \fq keys to death and the world of the dead: \ft That is, power over death and the world of the dead.\f*
\v 19 Write what you have seen and what is and what will happen after these things.
\v 20 I will explain the mystery of the seven stars that you saw at my right side and the seven gold lampstands. The seven stars are the angels\f + \fr 1.20 \fq angels: \ft Perhaps guardian angels that represent the churches, or they may be church leaders or messengers sent to the churches.\f* of the seven churches, and the lampstands are the seven churches.
